The Izyum area is getting increasingly confusing as there is little news but hints of changing control over various areas. It is possible that Ukraine has captured both Sulyhivka and Dovhenke. For now I have kept Sulyhivka as a gray area and Dovhenke as under Russian control. I am not confident about either. Today Ukraine identified a Russian recon group near Dovhenke and drove them away (3). This is a bit odd
column4: and hints towards a possible Ukrainian presence in the town. Similarly
column5: Russian recon was driven away from Dolyna (4).
